HEADWORD: Evirate
<hw>E"vi*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>eviratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>evirare</ets> to castrate;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>vir</ets> man.]</ety> <def>To emasculate; to
dispossess of manhood.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

